This paper focuses on human pose estimation using deep learning techniques, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed network architecture involves multiple stages and multi-scale fusions, which are typical techniques in deep learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the effectiveness of the proposed method compared to existing methods, which involves empirical evaluation and comparison, a common practice in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper uses keypoint heatmaps, which are commonly used in multimedia applications (cs.MM). Finally, the paper's focus on human pose estimation could also be relevant to robotics applications (cs.RO).
